name: Leaning on a Lamp Post
comments: George Formby first sang this song in the film "Feather Your Nest", released July 19, 1937 and directed by William Beaudine. This performance was after the song had already been performed by Val Rosing. The recording released as a single is not the same as in the film: in fact it was made after the film premiered.

Turtle Dove
comments: This performance is a version of "I'm Just a Country Boy" with the incorporation of a verse found in versions of "The Turtle Dove," an old English traditional song. Some English folk scholars trace these lyrics back to a broadside ballad, "The Languishing Lamentation of Two Loyal Lovers." The original lyrics of "I'm Just a Country Boy" also include a few lines similar to those found in "The Turtle Dove."
